Julie Stout: I remembered.

151
00:22:36.030 --> 00:23:00.020
Julie Stout: So he was able to record himself and everything, and give you that information. And he was virtually blind, so he was… this gave him really something to think about in his old age. Yeah. To remember positively, because he was… and he said, you mean my… this is going to be all over the United States? And actually, it's funny, because now it is. I can look on A Books, and there it is. There it is.

152
00:23:00.230 --> 00:23:02.330
Julie Stout: He couldn't believe it.

153
00:23:03.970 --> 00:23:05.040
Julie Stout: So…

154
00:23:05.390 --> 00:23:18.329
Julie Stout: Oh, when did you move to, Bloomington, then? Or you said you moved away from Indianapolis. Is there some… where did you go after Indianapolis? I got married. I got married when I was 22, right after finishing college.

