00:26:37.100 --> 00:26:53.139
Julie Stout: RVs, they had… they were… they were doing good. They had plenty of money. We went back some years later, and it had all changed. It completely changed. Can you remember what year that was? That you moved to Kentucky? Yeah, it was 72 that we moved down there, and 74 we came back.

183
00:26:53.510 --> 00:27:03.949
Julie Stout: the peak of the steel, like, era is in the 70s, so that makes perfect sense. And that's where I ended up writing my master's thesis, and in a…

